Subject: [PATCH 16/17] feat(theme): light / dark / professional palettes +
 sidebar switcher
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User wanted three themes that change all colors based on selection.

A. THREE PALETTES  (lib/theme.ts)
   - Dark: existing #0d1117/#161b22 amber/saffron palette
   - Light: white surfaces, slate text, ochre accent — readable on bright
     screens and for paper-like report sharing
   - Professional: Bloomberg-terminal style — pure black bg, orange highlights,
     all-mono typeface (Roboto Mono everywhere). Loud accents, no chrome.

B. ThemeContext + useTheme()  (contexts/ThemeContext.tsx)
   Hydrates from localStorage on mount (key 'mc-theme'); falls back to
   dark before hydration. On every theme change:
    - sets data-theme=X on <html> for global CSS hooks
    - exposes the palette as CSS custom properties (--mc-bg, --mc-text,
      --mc-accent, etc.) on document.documentElement so non-React components
      and global CSS can pick up the active theme

C. SIDEBAR SWITCHER  (components/ThemeSwitcher.tsx)
   Compact icon-button mode rendered above Settings in the sidebar — click
   cycles dark → light → professional → dark. Full pill-row mode also
   available for use on a settings page.

D. INDIAINSTITUTIONALREPORT migrated to useTheme()
   The main report component (BAJAJCON / KENNAMET / MTAR etc.) now reads
   colors from the theme palette inside the function body, shadowing the
   module-level dark constants. Switching theme in the sidebar instantly
   re-renders the entire report in the new palette. Other dashboard pages
   keep their hardcoded colors for now and can be migrated incrementally.

E. Providers wrap is in app/providers.tsx so the theme is available to
   every dashboard page from the moment it mounts.

After deploy, click the new 'Dark/Light/Pro' icon at the bottom of the
left sidebar to cycle palettes. Selection persists across reloads via
localStorage.

